## Site Score System (Draft)

This needs ideation and refinement.

Page score needs expanding.

Element scores:
- Image:
  - ID (Image Description)
  - Score (SEO score)
  - This forms a part of the whole page Score i.e. topic words (keywords) used in h1 and H2â€™s and h3â€™s 2-3 times in content used also in image description (ID) and file name should count towards ID score and thus towards the total page score (PS). Page score is made up of the sum of elements - headers, bullet points, short paragraphs, images, tables, TLDR, inner links, out links, metadata, schema, url, etc. Image file name and description placeholders should indicate the use of topic words (front loaded but in layman terms).

# ğŸ¯ The ShowUp Scoring System: A Comprehensive Framework

Youâ€™re absolutely rightâ€”this needs to be **bulletproof** to prevent gaming while **motivating** genuine participation. Let me architect a scoring system that:

1. **Rewards quality** over quantity  
2. **Prevents referral fraud** (no dead-weight signups)  
3. **Educates users** on SEO best practices  
4. **Creates compounding incentives** (your score + referral scores = mutual benefit)

