## ğŸ—ï¸ 1. PAGE QUALITY SCORE (0-700)

### **A. Technical SEO (0-200 per page)**

These are the **foundational elements**â€”if these fail, nothing else matters.

|Element              |Max Points|How Itâ€™s Scored                                               |
|---------------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Page Speed**       |30        |<2s = 30pts, 2-3s = 20pts, 3-4s = 10pts, >4s = 0pts           |
|**Mobile Responsive**|25        |Perfect mobile = 25pts, Issues = 10pts, Broken = 0pts         |
|**HTTPS/Security**   |20        |SSL active = 20pts, No SSL = 0pts                             |
|**Core Web Vitals**  |25        |All green = 25pts, 1 yellow = 15pts, Any red = 5pts           |
|**URL Structure**    |20        |Clean URL with keyword = 20pts, Generic = 10pts, Messy = 5pts |
|**Metadata Present** |20        |Title + Meta Desc + OG tags = 20pts, Missing any = 10pts      |
|**Schema Markup**    |20        |Proper schema = 20pts, Partial = 10pts, None = 0pts           |
|**XML Sitemap**      |20        |Present & submitted = 20pts, Present only = 10pts, None = 0pts|
|**Robots.txt**       |20        |Properly configured = 20pts, Default = 10pts, Blocking = 0pts |

**Total Technical SEO: 200 points**

-----

### **B. On-Page SEO (0-300 per page)**

This is where **keyword optimization** and **content structure** come in.

#### **Header Structure (0-60)**

|Element            |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                                                        |
|-------------------|----------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**H1 Tag**         |20        |Has target keyword + front-loaded = 20pts, keyword present = 15pts, no keyword = 5pts, missing = 0pts|
|**H2 Tags (2-4)**  |20        |2-4 H2s with variations of keyword = 20pts, 1-2 H2s = 10pts, None/too many = 5pts                    |
|**H3 Tags**        |10        |Supporting headers with related terms = 10pts, Generic = 5pts, None = 0pts                           |
|**Hierarchy Logic**|10        |Proper H1â†’H2â†’H3 flow = 10pts, Skipped levels = 5pts, Broken = 0pts                                   |

#### **Content Quality (0-80)**

|Element             |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                        |
|--------------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Word Count**      |20        |800-1500 words = 20pts, 500-800 = 15pts, 300-500 = 10pts, <300 = 5pts|
|**Keyword Density** |15        |2-3% = 15pts, 1-2% = 10pts, <1% or >4% = 5pts                        |
|**Readability**     |15        |Flesch score 60-70 = 15pts, 50-60 or 70-80 = 10pts, Outside = 5pts   |
|**Paragraph Length**|10        |2-4 sentences avg = 10pts, 5-6 = 7pts, >6 = 3pts                     |
|**Bullet Points**   |10        |Has 2+ lists = 10pts, 1 list = 5pts, None = 0pts                     |
|**TL;DR Section**   |10        |Present & concise = 10pts, Missing = 0pts                            |

#### **Image Optimization (0-80)**

This is **critical** and often overlooked. Letâ€™s break it down properly:

|Element              |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                                                                                         |
|---------------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**File Name**        |15        |Has target keyword (e.g., `estate-planning-austin.jpg`) = 15pts, Generic = 5pts, Random = 0pts                                        |
|**Alt Text**         |20        |Descriptive + keyword (e.g., â€œEstate planning documents with attorney in Austin officeâ€) = 20pts, Keyword only = 10pts, Missing = 0pts|
|**Image Description**|15        |Full sentence with context = 15pts, Short phrase = 8pts, None = 0pts                                                                  |
|**File Size**        |10        |<100KB = 10pts, 100-200KB = 7pts, >200KB = 3pts                                                                                       |
|**Format**           |10        |WebP = 10pts, PNG/JPG optimized = 7pts, Uncompressed = 3pts                                                                           |
|**Lazy Loading**     |10        |Enabled = 10pts, Disabled = 0pts                                                                                                      |

**Example of a PERFECT Image (80/80 points):**

```html
<img 
  src="estate-planning-attorney-consultation-austin.webp" 
  alt="Estate planning attorney meeting with family in modern Austin office to discuss wills and trusts"
  title="Professional estate planning consultation in Austin, TX"
  loading="lazy"
  width="800" 
  height="533"
/>
```

**File name breakdown:**

- âœ… Target keyword: â€œestate-planningâ€  
- âœ… Modifier: â€œattorney-consultationâ€  
- âœ… Location: â€œaustinâ€  
- âœ… Descriptive, not generic

**Alt text breakdown:**

- âœ… Natural language sentence  
- âœ… Target keyword included organically  
- âœ… Describes whatâ€™s actually in the image  
- âœ… Location mentioned for local SEO

#### **Internal & External Links (0-50)**

|Element           |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                |
|------------------|----------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Internal Links**|20        |3-5 relevant links = 20pts, 1-2 = 12pts, 0 or >8 = 5pts      |
|**External Links**|15        |1-3 authoritative sources = 15pts, None = 5pts, Spammy = 0pts|
|**Anchor Text**   |15        |Descriptive anchors = 15pts, Generic (â€œclick hereâ€) = 5pts   |

#### **Call-to-Action (0-30)**

|Element        |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                                   |
|---------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**CTA Present**|15        |Clear, above fold = 15pts, Below fold = 10pts, Missing = 0pts                   |
|**CTA Clarity**|15        |Action-oriented (â€œSchedule Consultationâ€) = 15pts, Generic (â€œLearn Moreâ€) = 8pts|

**Total On-Page SEO: 300 points**

-----

### **C. Content Quality (0-200 per page)**

This measures **user experience** and **engagement signals** (stuff Google actually cares about).

|Element                |Max Points|Scoring Logic                                                             |
|-----------------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Unique Content**     |40        |100% unique = 40pts, <90% = 20pts, Duplicate = 0pts                       |
|**Topic Coverage**     |30        |Answers user intent fully = 30pts, Partial = 15pts, Thin = 5pts           |
|**E-E-A-T Signals**    |30        |Author bio + credentials + citations = 30pts, Partial = 15pts, None = 0pts|
|**Freshness**          |20        |Updated <30 days = 20pts, 30-90 days = 15pts, >1 year = 5pts              |
|**Multimedia**         |20        |Video + images + infographics = 20pts, Images only = 10pts, None = 0pts   |
|**Engagement Elements**|20        |Tables, accordions, interactive = 20pts, Basic = 10pts, None = 0pts       |
|**Social Proof**       |20        |Testimonials/reviews on page = 20pts, None = 0pts                         |
|**FAQ Section**        |20        |Schema-marked FAQs = 20pts, Plain text = 10pts, None = 0pts               |

**Total Content Quality: 200 points**

-----

## ğŸ¤ 2. COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT SCORE (0-200)

This is where **Growth Alliance** mechanics kick in.

### **A. Backlinks Given (0-100)**

Youâ€™re incentivized to **give** backlinks to partners.

|Action                           |Points     |Max Cap            |
|---------------------------------|-----------|-------------------|
|Link to partnerâ€™s homepage       |5 pts each |25 pts (5 partners)|
|Link to partnerâ€™s service page   |8 pts each |40 pts (5 partners)|
|Write blog post featuring partner|15 pts each|30 pts (2 partners)|
|Guest post on partnerâ€™s site     |20 pts each|40 pts (2 partners)|

**Anti-Gaming Rules:**

- Links must be **contextually relevant** (AI checks)  
- Partner must **reciprocate** within 30 days or points decay  
- Maximum 5 partners for backlink exchange (quality > quantity)

### **B. Backlinks Received (0-100)**

Youâ€™re rewarded when partners link to **you**.

|Source                     |Points     |Max Cap            |
|---------------------------|-----------|-------------------|
|Partner homepage link      |10 pts each|50 pts (5 partners)|
|Partner blog mention       |15 pts each|45 pts (3 partners)|
|Guest post byline link     |25 pts each|50 pts (2 partners)|
|External (non-partner) link|5 pts each |25 pts (5 links)   |

**Quality Multipliers:**

- Partner has Site Score >500: **1.5x points**  
- Partner has Site Score >700: **2x points**  
- External link from DA 50+ site: **3x points**

**Why this works:**

- You want to partner with **high-quality** sites (they boost your score more)  
- Partners are incentivized to **improve their own scores** (so you get more points from them)  
- **Mutual growth** is built into the system

-----

## ğŸŒ 3. GROWTH ALLIANCE NETWORK SCORE (0-100)

This prevents referral spam and rewards **active, engaged referrals**.

### **A. Active Referrals (0-50)**

|Referral Status            |Points Each|Max Cap             |
|---------------------------|-----------|--------------------|
|Signed up + active 30 days |5 pts      |25 pts (5 referrals)|
|Signed up + active 90 days |8 pts      |40 pts (5 referrals)|
|Signed up + paid subscriber|10 pts     |50 pts (5 referrals)|

**Decay Rules:**

- If referral churns: **Lose those points immediately**  
- If referral is inactive >30 days: **50% point reduction**  
- If referral never completes site setup: **0 points**

### **B. Referral Quality Score (0-50)**

This is **critical** to prevent garbage referrals.

|Quality Metric                             |Points     |Logic                   |
|-------------------------------------------|-----------|------------------------|
|Referral Site Score >300                   |10 pts each|Max 30 pts (3 referrals)|
|Referral Site Score >500                   |15 pts each|Max 45 pts (3 referrals)|
|Referral Site Score >700                   |20 pts each|Max 60 pts (3 referrals)|
|Referral actively participates in community|5 pts each |Max 25 pts (5 referrals)|

**The Flywheel:**

- You refer someone â†’ They build a quality site â†’ Your score increases  
- They refer someone â†’ That person builds a quality site â†’ Your referralâ€™s score increases â†’ Your score increases (2nd order effect)

**This creates a natural selection system:** Only quality partners want to work with you because they know youâ€™ll help them succeed (and vice versa).

-----

## ğŸ“ˆ SITE SCORE CALCULATION

### **How It All Comes Together**

```javascript
function calculateSiteScore(site) {
  // 1. Average Page Quality across all pages
  const pageScores = site.pages.map(page => {
    const technical = calculateTechnicalSEO(page); // 0-200
    const onPage = calculateOnPageSEO(page);       // 0-300
    const content = calculateContentQuality(page);  // 0-200
    
    return technical + onPage + content; // Max 700 per page
  });
  
  const avgPageScore = pageScores.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / pageScores.length;
  
  // 2. Community Engagement
  const backlinksGiven = calculateBacklinksGiven(site);    // 0-100
  const backlinksReceived = calculateBacklinksReceived(site); // 0-100
  const communityScore = backlinksGiven + backlinksReceived; // Max 200
  
  // 3. Growth Alliance Network
  const activeReferrals = calculateActiveReferrals(site);  // 0-50
  const referralQuality = calculateReferralQuality(site);  // 0-50
  const networkScore = activeReferrals + referralQuality;  // Max 100
  
  // Total Site Score
  const totalScore = avgPageScore + communityScore + networkScore;
  
  return {
    total: Math.round(totalScore), // 0-1000
    breakdown: {
      pageQuality: Math.round(avgPageScore),
      community: Math.round(communityScore),
      network: Math.round(networkScore)
    },
    pages: pageScores.length
  };
}
```

-----

## ğŸ¯ MINIMUM VIABILITY THRESHOLDS

To prevent gaming, **referral rewards** only apply when **both parties** meet minimums:

|Tier        |Min Site Score|Min Pages|Min Community|Referral Benefit       |
|------------|--------------|---------|-------------|-----------------------|
|**Bronze**  |300           |3        |20 pts       |5% discount            |
|**Silver**  |500           |5        |50 pts       |10% discount           |
|**Gold**    |700           |8        |100 pts      |20% discount + features|
|**Platinum**|850           |10+      |150 pts      |Free + commission      |

**Example Scenario:**

**Jacques (Site Score: 750)**

- Refers Sarah  
- Sarah signs up but only has Site Score: 200 (incomplete site)  
- **Jacques gets: 0% discount** (Sarah below Bronze threshold)

**Two months later:**

- Sarah completes her site â†’ Site Score: 520 (Silver tier)  
- **Jacques now gets: 10% discount**  
- Sarah also gets 10% discount (mutual benefit)

**Why this works:**

- No incentive to refer low-quality leads  
- Referrer is motivated to **help** referee succeed  
- System rewards **collaboration**, not just signups

